pageContext.description: On the inside there is a seam down centre of face; on the outside down sides, past loop as usual. A little light coloured earth adheres, especially inside socket.
pageContext.collection: Maidstone Museum,Bought from Mr. W. C. Wells, Sudbury, Harrow (1917)
pageContext.site: England,Kent,Whitstable,Brought up by oyster dredgers nearly a mile from shore.
pageContext.remarks: In a letter, dated 24.vi.16, Mr. Wells says "I have in my collection 3 bronze socketed axes, which were found at Whitstable. They were brought up by oyster dredgers nearly a mile from shore. I understand that the oyster dredgers know the exact spot where they are found, and look out for specimens."
